This is a great story on the trial of experimental Ebola treatments whose results we are all getting so excited about today. Amy [Maxmen] is one of the few journalists who has actually gone to North Kivu to report on this outbreak, a dangerous and critically important job!

Amy Maxmen@amymaxmen:
This #Ebola trial in #DRC is absolutely remarkable. It's scientifically rigorous but also adaptable. If an attack happens nearby, frontline responders alter protocols. If you missed it, I wrote about the unprecedented process of doing science in a warzone: Maxmen A. Science under fire: Ebola researchers fight to test drugs and vaccines in a war zone. 24 Jul 2019 https://www.nature.com/articles/d41586-019-02258-4 (recommended reading - Mod.LK)].

