[2] Response

- Mon 12 Aug 2019
[Radio Okapi]
https://www.radiookapi.net/2019/08/12/actualite/sante/la-grande-barriere-de-goma-les-controle-dacces-sur-le-territoire-rwandais

At the Great Barrier Goma, access control on Rwandan territory is harsher
-------------------------
Restrictions on entry into Rwanda by the Goma-Gisenyi border post have been strengthened. Last week, Rwandan and Congolese citizens living in Gisenyi either experienced difficulties or were prevented from entering Rwanda or the DRC.

On Sun 11 Aug 2019, even some international officials paid for these measures.

A Beninese resident in Goma, an international civil servant in an organization active in North Kivu province, was prevented from entering Rwanda where he was driving his children for health care. He states that he "no longer understands this tightening of entry measures in Rwanda, whereas, according to him, Rwandan immigration services are relatively comprehensive when it comes to international civil servants".

Hundreds of travelers suffered the same fate on Sun [11 Aug 2019] at the border between Rwanda and the DRC.

Last week, several Congolese living in Gisenyi declared that they lived "[in] stress" with the strict filtering of entrances and exits at the 2 border posts between Gisenyi and Goma. Some even had to decide to move back to Goma, a city they left for security reasons or more attractive rents on the Rwandan side.

In its recommendations, by declaring Ebola in the DRC an epidemic of international emergency, WHO had nevertheless recommended to the national authorities of border states not to use it to hinder migratory movements in the region.

