- Tue 13 Aug 2019
[Actualite, on-line trans. edited]
https://actualite.cd/2019/08/13/rdc-ebola-une-manifestation-contre-les-equipes-de-riposte-signalee-goma

DRC-Ebola: protest against the response teams reported in Goma
----------------
A strong tension is being observed, Tue 13 Aug 2019, in the district Majengo, in the municipality of Karisimbi, north of Goma. At the base, some angry residents are protesting the arrival of a response team at a clinic where a woman who came from Kiwanja, in Rutshuru territory, died.

"Young people barricaded the road from the entrance, Three Lamps to Majengo, before reaching Buhene. They attacked any Land Cruiser thinking they had teams on board. They say that Ebola is a business imported from Beni-Butembo to Goma. Now, I have seen elements of the force of the order moving there, maybe to calm things down, "says a resident who is at the site of the demonstration.

"I heard a few shots," the same source added. The outbreak comes as 2 Ebola cases have been declared cured and have left the Ebola treatment center in Goma.

At his last press conference, before resigning from the Ministry of Health, Dr. Oly Ilunga demanded that tests be done on all the deaths that will be recorded in the city of Goma and about to prevent the spread of the disease. The city of Goma recorded its 1st case of Ebola on 14 Jul 2019.

[Byline: Jonathan Kombi]

